    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I thought about doing it, but my plan is to get rid of the readline based interface soon - that was a big part of the rationale for adopting prompt toolkit. I don't want to support both interfaces in a release, so any flag would only be in the development version, and I'm not sure it's worth it. It's a one line change in ipapp to use the old TerminalInteractiveShell class for now.\n\nIs this prompted by a problem in the new interface? The idea of landing it is to discover and fix any problems, so I don't want to make it too easy to switch back.\n"
  },
