    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You can select a pygments theme directly with the `highlighting_style` config option. Run `list(pygments.styles.get_all_styles())` to see the options.\n\nI tried to make the default theme visible on both light and dark terminals (there's no way to detect which we're on). I tested it on both backgrounds on my machines, but it's probably going to look a bit different in different terminal emulators. Obviously we can do further tweaking, but we need to test in both: we can't just optimise for one background and make it illegible in the other.\n\nI also know that the compromises to make it work in both don't make it great in either, which is why I made sure it's easy to select other themes.\n"
  },
