    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "No I don't want Pygments Styles, they hardcode extended escape sequences to RGB values (`\\x01b[38;2;r;g;b;m.`) explicitly.\nWhile our theming emits `\\x01b[30` to `\\x01b[37` which can be mapped:\n\n![ansi](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/335567/13236261/264e0638-d978-11e5-88a2-572d290615c5.gif)\n\nThis is not (yet) possible with Prompt-toolkit, unless you use Pygments master and Prompt_toolkit [master of next week](https://github.com/jonathanslenders/python-prompt-toolkit/pull/240).\n\nRight now locally with all of dev version I can use a custom style like:\n\n```\nclass LightBG(Style):\n\n    styles = {\n        Token.Prompt: '#ansiblue',\n        }\n```\n\nWhich works, but that's painful. \n\nAnd also the theme should not be unicode, we should allow a dotted object name. \n\nThese are exactly the reasons my my other Pygments PR took so long, to get around this limitation. \n"
  },
