    "created_at": "2016-02-23T00:02:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-02-23T00:02:40Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If we're going to be adopting pygments throughout, I don't want to define our own styling system, we should just use what's in pygments. If you're improving that, so much the better.\n\nYou can define extra named [pygments styles using entry points](http://pygments.org/docs/plugins/#entrypoints), and you can also add your own mapping of overrides in the config file, so I don't think we need to deal with object names for styles as well. There's plenty of flexibility already.\n"
  },
